I hope this isn't a terribly stupid question:  i understand that with
an x-byte length repeating xor key one can retrieve the original plaintext
xor'd by itself by shifting the xor'd text by the length of the key and
xor'ing itself.  iow (if i understand correctly): ABC xored by unknown 1 
byte key=XXX...="XYZ", then, .
 by shifting xyz (=YZX)and xor'ing the texts (XYZ xor YZX) one is left
 with is ABC
xor'd by BCA. THEN WHAT?  how does one get from (A xor B) back to A 
withoutknowing A or B??? )
